cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper belongs to the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it analyzes linguistic networks generated from texts. The use of complex network analysis methods suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The comparison of Croatian syllable networks with Portuguese and Chinese syllable networks may indicate a focus on cross-linguistic analysis, which could place it in the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.LG). The use of clustering coefficient and small world networks suggests a focus on network science (cs.SD), while the comparison of different language networks may indicate a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.NE).
